  "chapter": {
    "number": 39,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "I Will Watch My Ways"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. For Jeduthun. A Psalm of David."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I said, “I will watch my ways",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that I will not sin with my tongue;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will guard my mouth with a muzzle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as long as the wicked are present.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I was speechless and still;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I remained silent, even from speaking good,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and my sorrow was stirred.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My heart grew hot within me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as I mused, the fire burned.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Then I spoke with my tongue:",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Show me, O LORD, my end",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the measure of my days.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let me know how fleeting my life is.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You, indeed, have made my days as handbreadths,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my lifetime as nothing before You.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Truly each man at his best",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "exists as but a breath.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely every man goes about like a phantom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "surely he bustles in vain;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he heaps up riches",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not knowing who will haul them away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And now, O Lord, for what do I wait?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My hope is in You.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Deliver me from all my transgressions;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not make me the reproach of fools.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have become mute;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I do not open my mouth",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because of what You have done.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remove Your scourge from me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am perishing by the force of Your hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You discipline and correct a man for his iniquity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "consuming like a moth what he holds dear;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "surely each man is but a vapor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear my prayer, O LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and give ear to my cry for help;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be deaf to my weeping.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For I am a foreigner dwelling with You,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a stranger like all my fathers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn Your gaze away from me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that I may again be cheered",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "before I depart and am no more.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
